WEBVTT

00:23.620 --> 00:28.420
Be ye followers of me, even as I also am of Christ.

00:28.420 --> 00:34.240
Now I praise you, brethren, that ye remember me in all things, and keep the ordinances,

00:34.440 --> 00:36.500
as I have delivered them to you.

00:36.960 --> 00:42.140
But I would have you know, that the head of every man is Christ, and the head of the woman

00:42.140 --> 00:45.260
is the man, and the head of Christ is God.

00:45.760 --> 00:51.260
Every man praying or prophesying, having his head covered, dishonoreth his head.

00:51.680 --> 00:57.240
But every woman that prayeth or prophesieth with her head uncovered, dishonoreth her head.

00:57.240 --> 01:01.520
For that is even all one, as if she were shaven.

01:01.960 --> 01:05.560
For if the woman be not covered, let her also be shorn.

01:05.960 --> 01:10.540
But if it be a shame for a woman to be shorn or shaven, let her be covered.

01:11.300 --> 01:16.520
For a man indeed ought not to cover his head, for as much as he is the image and glory of

01:16.520 --> 01:20.200
God, but the woman is the glory of the man.

01:20.880 --> 01:24.520
For the man is not of the woman, but the woman of the man.

01:24.960 --> 01:28.740
Neither was the man created for the woman, but the woman for the man.

01:29.180 --> 01:34.800
For this cause ought the woman to have power on her head because of the angels.

01:35.660 --> 01:41.020
Nevertheless, neither is the man without the woman, neither the woman without the man in

01:41.020 --> 01:41.560
the Lord.

01:42.120 --> 01:48.640
For as the woman is of the man, even so the man also by the woman, but all things of God.

01:48.640 --> 01:53.480
Judge in yourselves, is it comely that a woman pray into God uncovered?

01:54.480 --> 01:59.960
Doth not even nature itself teach you that if a man have long hair it is a shame to him?

02:00.620 --> 02:07.300
But if a woman have long hair, it is a glory to her, for her hair is given her for a covering.

02:08.000 --> 02:13.880
But if any man seem to be contentious, we have no such custom, neither the churches

02:13.880 --> 02:14.540
of God.

02:15.580 --> 02:22.020
Now in this that I declare unto you, I praise you not, that ye come together not for the

02:22.020 --> 02:23.600
better, but for the worse.

02:24.500 --> 02:29.280
For first of all, when ye come together in the church, I hear that there be divisions

02:29.280 --> 02:31.540
among you, and I partly believe it.

02:32.080 --> 02:38.080
For there must be also heresies among you, that they which are approved may be made manifest

02:38.080 --> 02:39.060
among you.

02:39.760 --> 02:44.780
When ye come together therefore into one place, this is not to eat the Lord's supper.

02:45.960 --> 02:52.400
For in eating every one taketh before other his own supper, and one is hungry, and another

02:52.400 --> 02:53.200
is drunken.

02:53.980 --> 02:58.040
What have ye not houses to eat and to drink in?

02:58.560 --> 03:02.800
Or despise ye the church of God, and shame them that have not?

03:03.620 --> 03:05.640
What shall I say to you?

03:05.900 --> 03:07.420
Shall I praise you in this?

03:07.420 --> 03:09.540
I praise you not.

03:10.260 --> 03:16.740
For I have received of the Lord that which also I delivered unto you, that the Lord Jesus,

03:17.060 --> 03:20.220
the same night in which he was betrayed, took bread.

03:20.860 --> 03:25.240
And when he had given thanks, he break it, and said, Take eat.

03:25.700 --> 03:28.980
This is my body, which is broken for you.

03:29.680 --> 03:31.720
This do in remembrance of me.

03:32.420 --> 03:38.240
After the same manner also, he took the cup when he had supped, saying, This cup is the

03:38.240 --> 03:40.340
New Testament in my blood.

03:41.000 --> 03:45.200
This do ye as oft as ye drink it in remembrance of me.

03:45.680 --> 03:51.580
For as often as ye eat this bread and drink this cup, ye do show the Lord's death till

03:51.580 --> 03:52.140
he come.

03:53.160 --> 03:58.080
Wherefore whosoever shall eat this bread and drink this cup of the Lord unworthily shall

03:58.080 --> 04:01.200
be guilty of the body and blood of the Lord.

04:02.000 --> 04:07.660
But let a man examine himself, and so let him eat of that bread and drink of that cup.

04:08.480 --> 04:14.120
For he that eateth and drinketh unworthily eateth and drinketh damnation to himself,

04:14.540 --> 04:16.260
not discerning the Lord's body.

04:16.920 --> 04:21.420
For this cause many are weak and sickly among you, and many sleep.

04:22.220 --> 04:25.580
For if we would judge ourselves, we should not be judged.

04:26.460 --> 04:31.860
But when we are judged, we are chastened of the Lord, that we should not be condemned

04:31.860 --> 04:32.920
with the world.

04:33.800 --> 04:38.300
Wherefore, my brethren, when ye come together to eat, tarry one for another.

04:38.880 --> 04:45.180
And if any man hunger, let him eat at home, that ye come not together unto condemnation.

04:45.580 --> 04:48.580
And the rest I will set in order when I come.

04:49.080 --> 04:50.500
Chapter 12

04:50.500 --> 04:54.860
Now concerning spiritual gifts, brethren, I would not have you ignorant.

04:55.920 --> 05:02.400
Ye know that ye were Gentiles carried away unto these dumb idols, even as ye were led.

05:03.080 --> 05:08.940
Wherefore I give you to understand that no man speaking by the Spirit of God calleth

05:08.940 --> 05:15.280
Jesus accursed, and that no man can say that Jesus is the Lord, but by the Holy Ghost.

05:15.840 --> 05:19.720
Now there are diversities of gifts, but the same Spirit.

05:20.360 --> 05:23.860
And there are differences of administrations, but the same Lord.

05:24.480 --> 05:30.540
And there are diversities of operations, but it is the same God which worketh all in all.

05:31.320 --> 05:36.680
But the manifestation of the Spirit is given to every man to profit withal.

05:37.580 --> 05:42.700
For to one is given by the Spirit the word of wisdom, to another the word of knowledge

05:42.700 --> 05:48.300
by the same Spirit, to another faith by the same Spirit, to another the gifts of healing

05:48.300 --> 05:55.040
by the same Spirit, to another the working of miracles, to another prophecy, to another

05:55.040 --> 06:01.920
discerning of spirits, to another diverse kinds of tongues, to another the interpretation

06:01.920 --> 06:02.620
of tongues.

06:03.520 --> 06:11.260
But all these worketh that one and the self same Spirit, dividing to every man severally

06:11.260 --> 06:12.040
as he will.

06:12.720 --> 06:18.420
For as the body is one, and hath many members, and all the members of that one body being

06:18.420 --> 06:22.420
many are one body, so also is Christ.

06:23.080 --> 06:29.080
For by one Spirit we are all baptized into one body, whether we be Jews or Gentiles,

06:29.400 --> 06:34.880
whether we be bond or free, and have been all made to drink into one Spirit.

06:35.400 --> 06:38.200
For the body is not one member, but many.

06:38.680 --> 06:45.020
If the foot shall say, Because I am not the hand, I am not of the body, Is it therefore

06:45.020 --> 06:46.140
not of the body?

06:46.740 --> 06:53.360
And if the ear shall say, Because I am not the eye, I am not of the body, Is it therefore

06:53.360 --> 06:54.420
not of the body?

06:54.980 --> 06:58.140
If the whole body were an eye, where were the hearing?

06:58.920 --> 07:02.200
If the whole were hearing, where were the smelling?

07:02.200 --> 07:08.260
But now hath God set the members, every one of them, in the body, as it hath pleased him.

07:08.720 --> 07:12.160
And if they were all one member, where were the body?

07:12.700 --> 07:16.540
But now are they many members, yet but one body.

07:17.300 --> 07:22.640
And the eye cannot say unto the hand, I have no need of thee, nor again the head to the

07:22.640 --> 07:24.800
feet, I have no need of you.

07:25.560 --> 07:31.660
Nay, much more those members of the body which seem to be more feeble are necessary.

07:32.400 --> 07:38.880
And those members of the body which we think to be less honourable, upon these we bestow

07:38.880 --> 07:40.160
more abundant honour.

07:40.780 --> 07:44.740
And our uncomely parts have more abundant comeliness.

07:45.780 --> 07:52.020
For our comely parts have no need, but God hath tempered the body together, having given

07:52.020 --> 07:54.980
more abundant honour to that part which lacked.

07:55.800 --> 08:00.300
That there should be no schism in the body, but that the members should have the same

08:00.300 --> 08:02.000
care one for another.

08:03.180 --> 08:07.240
And whether one member suffer, all the members suffer with it.

08:07.540 --> 08:11.620
Or when member be honoured, all the members rejoice with it.

08:11.980 --> 08:16.180
Now ye are the body of Christ, and members in particular.

08:16.180 --> 08:23.700
And God hath set some in the church, first apostles, secondarily prophets, thirdly teachers,

08:24.220 --> 08:31.380
after that miracles, then gifts of healings, helps, governments, diversities of tongues.

08:32.100 --> 08:33.360
Are all apostles?

08:33.700 --> 08:34.600
Are all prophets?

08:34.940 --> 08:35.860
Are all teachers?

08:36.320 --> 08:38.080
Are all workers of miracles?

08:38.680 --> 08:40.100
Have all the gifts of healing?

08:40.660 --> 08:42.180
Do all speak with tongues?

08:42.820 --> 08:44.080
Do all interpret?

08:44.080 --> 08:52.440
But covet earnestly the best gifts, and yet show I unto you a more excellent way.

